cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on indoor localization and tracking of mobile devices using WiFi technology, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel deep LOS/NLOS classifier using the Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI), which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the problem of indoor localization and tracking, which can be considered as a computer vision and pattern recognition problem. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed framework can be used for tracking robots in indoor environments, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a framework for indoor localization and tracking, which involves control systems and signal processing techniques.
